    "Intuition: Factorization takes advantage of matrices with few signal areas by focusing computation only on those areas.",
    "Operating on smaller sub-matrices that have signal allows the model to scale to longer input sequences while maintaining its efficiency in capturing relevant information.",
    "The tradeoff is that sparse attention matrices may lose some information or signal, resulting in reduced expressiveness.",
    "Therefore, alternating layers between full and sparse attention results in an acceptable compromise between performance and computational cost.",
